<item>
            <title>[LU-7296] &quot;lock timed out&quot; console messages are not useful</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7296</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;ldlm_expired_completion_wait()&lt;/tt&gt; there is a useless &lt;tt&gt;LCONSOLE_WARN()&lt;/tt&gt; statement that prints &quot;lock timed out (enqued at T, Ds ago)&quot; which is followed by a &lt;tt&gt;LDLM_DEBUG()&lt;/tt&gt; statement that prints the lock but not to the console or to the dmesg buffer. The console warning should be eliminated and the debug statement upgraded to an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
